      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "Note"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "SPEECH-GOD - character dialogue TTS (F5-TTS / Fish Speech)\n\n1. ENGINE: pick f5-tts or fish-speech in the Loader. F5-TTS is the\n   lighter, easier install; Fish Speech adds inline emotion markers.\n2. CHARACTERS: rename character_name in each Character node to YOUR\n   character (e.g. ZIKKI, ZUMBOO, NARRATOR) and set gender/age/tone/\n   energy/speed + micro sliders. Unused Character nodes? Ctrl+B them\n   and unplug from Cast - or chain another Cast node for more than 4.\n3. DIALOGUE: write a script in the Generate node. Tags must match the\n   character_name values (case-insensitive). Formats:\n      [ZIKKI]               or       ZIKKI: Hey Zumboo!\n      Hey Zumboo!\n   Untagged text = single-voice mode (first character speaks).\n4. OPTIONAL inputs (purple LoadAudio nodes, Ctrl+B to enable):\n   - Voice Reference: clone any speaker from a 5-15s clip\n   - Emotion Reference: borrow pacing/emotion from another clip\n   - Emotion Blend node: e.g. 70% happy + 30% excited\n5. NO REFERENCE? Drop seed voices into\n   custom_nodes/ComfyUI-SpeechGod/assets/default_voices/\n   (see README.txt there) - cloning engines always need some voice.\n6. TAKES: set takes=2..8 for alternate deliveries (batched output).\n   variation_strength controls how different takes sound.\n7. CONSISTENCY: 'Save Character' writes characters/<name>.json+.voice;\n   reload with 'Load Character' in any other workflow/episode.\n8. Post Process: normalize/compress/limit on by default; NR, EQ,\n   de-breath, silence trim toggleable.\n9. Export: wav/flac/mp3 at 22050/44100/48000."
      ],
      "title": "📖 SPEECH-GOD - HOW TO USE",
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    }
